ngcb28 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24120844/Web_Blizzard_MRiga_BritishColumbia-19-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 630w\"></a></p><p>Rocky Mountain has been pushing the limits with fat bikes for years now, and the latest Blizzard looks like a continuation of that. We’ve seen 27.5″ fat bike wheels and tires creep their way into the fat bike world, and now the Blizzard is joining in—though it’s also still compatible with 26 x 5.0″ wheels and tires for those who prefer the most flotation over rollover improvements offered by the bigger wheels.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022.jpg\" alt=\"Rocky Mountain Blizzard 2022 geometry\" width=\"1072\" height=\"568\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022.jpg 1072w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022-297x157.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022-800x424.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022-120x64.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022-768x407.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022-696x369.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022-1068x566.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022-793x420.jpg 793w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1072px) 100vw, 1072px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022.jpg 1072w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022-297x157.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022-800x424.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022-120x64.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022-768x407.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022-696x369.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022-1068x566.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/24124419/Rocky-Mountain-blizzard-275-2022-793x420.jpg 793w\"></a></p><p>Sold with a rigid fork, the frames are compatible with a 100mm travel suspension fork and 27.5″ wheels or up to a 120mm travel suspension fork with 26″ wheels. The Smoothwall Carbon frame has been lengthened and slackened with a 66° head tube angle, and 425-500mm reach numbers d